         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [Just as remembrance ceremonies in honour of the late Kaiser Wilhelm ¶  in the remotest regions bore a magnificent character, so do the reports sent us by Mr Ferd. von Müller, Melbourne. ¶  He also...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">88.04.00d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Gartenflora</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gartenflora</seg>, vol. 37 (1888), p. 295. The issue in which it appeared is probably the first of two issues for June, although the unusual publication pattern, with one issue of 48 pages and two of 56 pages included in the 22 issues for the year, makes this a little uncertain. The probable last date of sending the letter is April.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[<seg style="">Wie auch in den fernsten Gegenden die Gedächtnisfeiern zu Ehren des hochseligen Kaisers </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Wilhelm</seg>
               <seg style=""> einen grossartigen Charakter trugen, geht so recht aus den Berichten hervor, die Herr </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Ferd. von Müller</seg>
               <seg style="">, Melbourne, uns übermittelt hat. Derselbe übersandte auch eine grosse, trefflich gelungene Lithographie, das Antlitz S M. des Kaisers </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Wilhelm</seg>
               <seg style=""> in Lebensgrösse vorzüglich wiedergebend.] </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; line-height: 0.1945in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Just as remembrance ceremonies in honour of the late Kaiser Wilhelm<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Kaiser Wilhelm I died on 9 March 1888, in Berlin.</p>
               </note> in the remotest regions bore a magnificent character, so do the reports sent us by Mr Ferd. von Müller, Melbourne.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M was one of the principal speakers at the mourning function for Kaiser Wilhelm held in Melbourne, see 'Die Trauer um Kaiser Wilhelm in Melbourne' [The mourning for Kaiser Wilhelm in Melbourne], <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Australische Zeitung</seg> (Adelaide), 21 March 1888, p. 1.</p>
               </note> He also sent a large, well-executed lithograph, excellently rendering the face of the Kaiser Wilhelm in life size.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No copy of this picture has been located.</p>
               </note>]</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
